                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/264</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Francisco Sugar Company, 112 Wall Street, New York, states that cane burnt on
                    their property represents loss of over 2,200,000 dollars. They request further
                    protection for their property, and are filing claim against Government of Cuba.
                    Bring this matter attention of President Menocal and request Cuban Government
                    give protection to this property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
